   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 193, recto: (1) Pamonthes, son of Patemis, together with Paeris, son of Totoes, (2) we say to Patemis, son of Belef: You have loaned (3) us your cow for one month of plowing, (4) makes 30 days of plowing, for 4 artabas of wheat, (5) their half, 2 artabas of wheat / 4 artabas of wheat again; (6) 2 artabas in [winter], by the maje-measure (7) of Sisois, (and) 2 artabas in the summer, (8) by the maje-measure of Sisois. (9) If the cow perishes, (10) we shall give you 3 staters besides ... (11) ...</ab>
         </div>
